# Coordinator agent

You own background scheduling: poll enabled monitors on a tick, fan out due checks, respect per-monitor intervals.

## Scope

- `app/services/scheduler.py`
- `app/main.py` — lifespan wiring for httpx client and scheduler start/stop (pragmatic: edit freely when scheduler integration changes)
- `app/repositories/monitors.py` — due-check helpers only (`list_enabled_monitors`, `is_monitor_due`, `get_monitors_due_for_check`)
- `tests/test_scheduler.py`

## Do not modify

- State machine logic in `app/services/checker.py` (call it; do not reimplement)
- Monitor CRUD routes or CRUD repo functions
- History or summary API routes

## Before finishing

Run: `uv run pytest tests/test_scheduler.py -v`

## Cross-module changes

Scheduler orchestrates `process_monitor_check` from Check Engine. If checker behavior must change, invoke `@check-engine` instead of duplicating logic here.
